  tables: SPF<=6000001, 7702 TD primes <= 78500, twin table <= 10^6 (0.0s)
== frontier: maximal twin-free intervals between consecutive twin centers ==
PRE-REGISTRATION (logged BEFORE any measurement):
  Interval: consecutive twin centers a < b; LENGTH L = b - a (the gap);
    interior roots a < m < b (count L-1; L=1 = adjacent twins, no interior).
  Scales: [1,10^6] exhaustive; windows [10^9,10^9+5e4) and [10^12,10^12+5e4)
    (intervals between consecutive twins INSIDE each window; edge parts dropped).
  ASSERT-FIRST base census at 10^6: 37915 centers -> 37914 intervals;
    histogram {0:32463, 50:4726, 100:626, 150:87, 200:10, 250:2}; 725 with
    L>=100; max L=255 after m=811652 -- any mismatch stops the stage.
  Trajectory: canonical grave rule (left-wing-first minFac,
    GenealogyBasins.canonicalPeel mirror; tier-general via fac_distinct).
    Exit = FIRST canonical step with target t <= a; penetration = a - t;
    first-peel-exit = [first target <= a]; drop ratio of the exiting step =
    (m_exit - t_exit)/L.
  SELFTEST (mandatory, STOP on violation): every step 1 <= t < cur; pre-exit
    nodes stay inside (a,b) and are twin-free; every exit lands t <= a
    (numeric shadow of the green theorem twinFree_descent_exit); every grave
    is a twin center <= a.
  OBSERVABLES (registered here, before measurement):
    O1 landing-twin (canonical grave) distribution per interval; entropy H
       (bits) and normalized Hn = H/log2(L-1) (L>=3).
    O2 penetration a - t per exit: per-interval mean; scale-free (a-t)/a.
    O3 distinct graves per interval G; scatter G/(L-1) (prior: basins
       adjacent-pair boundary density 0.9579 -> strong scatter, ratio near 1).
    O4 share of interior roots whose FIRST peel already exits (t1 <= a).
       A-priori note: every peel divides the center by >= ~5 while L stays
       a few hundred << a at these scales, so the registered expectation is
       share == 1 identically; any deviation is an anomaly.
    O5 drop ratio (m_exit - t_exit)/L per root; per-interval mean and max.
  STRATA: DEC = top decile by length (thr = sorted(L)[floor(0.9*(n-1))], take
    L >= thr); LONG = L >= 100; MED = |L - floor(median)| <= 2. Trajectory
    observables on DEC u LONG u MED; defect-linked comparison = LONG vs MED
    at the same scale, Welch z per observable.
  REACH-SETS: full BFS reach (arbitrary peel steps, node cap 200 = basins
    convention) for EVERY interior root of DEC intervals; DESCRIPTIVE
    summaries only (mean size, capped share, twins-in-reach, union-twins vs G).
  BUDGET: TIME_CAP 5400s per scale; overruns skip remaining items with a LOGGED
    note. Factorization tiers as in census9/census12; completeness reported.
  selftest: canonical_next_any == canonical_next (SPF rule) on all non-twin m <= 20000 -> PASS
